# MMA Coach AI

A full-stack athlete management application built with **ASP.NET Core**, **Entity Framework Core**, **Blazor Server**, and the **OpenAI API**. The application helps MMA coaches manage athletes, track training data, analyze performance, and generate AI-assisted coaching recommendations.

---

# Overview

MMA Coach AI is a portfolio project that demonstrates modern full-stack .NET development. The application allows coaches to manage athletes, record training information, analyze athlete performance through calculated metrics, and generate personalized coaching recommendations using AI.

The project follows a layered architecture that separates business logic, data access, and presentation, reflecting common software engineering practices used in production applications.

---

# Features

## Athlete Management

* Create, view, update, and delete athletes
* Associate athletes with coaches
* Store athlete information including:

  * Name
  * Nickname
  * Weight
  * Stance
  * Experience
  * Coach notes

## Coach Management

* Create and manage coaches
* Assign athletes to coaches

## Training Sessions

* Record athlete training sessions
* Store session date, duration, and notes

## Skill Ratings

Track athlete proficiency across multiple disciplines, including:

* Boxing
* Wrestling
* Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu
* Muay Thai
* Kickboxing
* Clinch Work

---

# Athlete Profiles

Each athlete has a dedicated profile page displaying:

* Coach information
* Skill ratings
* Training session history
* Total number of training sessions
* Average training session length
* Highest rated skill
* Lowest rated skill

These metrics are calculated dynamically within the service layer instead of being stored directly in the database.

---

# AI Coaching Recommendations

The application integrates with the OpenAI API to generate personalized coaching recommendations based on an athlete's profile.

The AI evaluates information such as:

* Coach assignment
* Highest and lowest rated skills
* Training frequency
* Average training session duration

This demonstrates how external AI services can be integrated into a traditional CRUD application while keeping the AI functionality isolated behind a dedicated service layer.

---

# Architecture

The application follows a layered architecture to separate responsibilities and improve maintainability.

```text
Blazor Server UI
        │
        ▼
ASP.NET Core Web API
        │
        ▼
Service Layer
        │
        ▼
Entity Framework Core
        │
        ▼
SQL Server
```

## Project Structure

```text
mmacoachai.api
├── Controllers
├── Services
└── Program.cs

mmacoachai.core
├── DTOs
├── Entities
└── Mappers

mmacoachai.infrastructure
└── Data
    └── AppDbContext

mmacoachai.client
├── Components
├── Models
├── Services
└── wwwroot
```

